'''Pashna Starkiller''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] who served as a respected [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[General/Legends|general]] who received the title [[Warlord of the Empire]]. Coming out of retirement, Starkiller was approached by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] at a time when it sought experienced leaders to help formulate strategy for its new [[Alliance Military/Legends|military]]. Starkiller defected to the Alliance's cause, and rose to become one of the Alliance's highest-ranked members. A seasoned military [[Officer/Legends|officer]], Starkiller's skills helped shape Rebel Alliance military planning. As a younger generation of military men and women rose, Starkiller relinquished some of the responsibility, while continuing to advise the Rebellion on strategic matters. In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], Starkiller was present in the ceremony held in honor of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and other [[Heroes of Yavin/Legends|heroes]] of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]].

In time, Starkiller retired again, only to be called upon by famed Rebel strategist [[Jan Dodonna/Legends|Jan Dodonna]] during the fight against the resurrected [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. Starkiller joined a number of other retired officers, including [[Vanden Willard/Legends|Vanden Willard]] and [[Adar Tallon/Legends|Adar Tallon]], in an advisory body that called itself the "[[Gray Cadre/Legends|Gray Cadre]]." Providing strategic planning for what was now the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], Starkiller and the others in the group were responsible for saving millions of lives in the war. When that [[Operation Shadow Hand|crisis]] was averted, Starkiller returned to a state of semi-retirement, continuing to receive intelligence briefings and regularly meeting with Dodonna and the others to advise the New Republic on its continuing [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|war]] against the Empire.

==Biography==
===Rebellion===
A [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="Insider" /> [[Gender/Legends|male]],<ref name="DESB" /> Pashna Starkiller was a respected [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[General/Legends|general]], and recipient of the elite title of [[Warlord of the Empire]].<ref name="Warlords" /> Starkiller ultimately retired as a [[Surface Marshal|Marshal]] early in the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="RoE" /> When approached by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], Starkiller defected to their cause.<ref name="Warlords" /> With Starkiller's help and that of several fellow [[Officer/Legends|officers]] recruited into the Alliance, Rebel military doctrine was transformed from the vague idealism it had been founded on into that of a true fighting force.<ref name="RoE" /> Starkiller rose to become one of the highest-ranking members of the Rebel Alliance. In this time, Starkiller participated in a number of field missions with a young tactical genius named [[Risiev Credal]].<ref name="AIR">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]''</ref>

In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]],<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> the Alliance achieved a major [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|victory]] at [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin IV]] when [[Rebel pilot/Legends|Rebel pilot]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] destroyed the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]] by firing [[Proton torpedo/Legends|proton torpedoes]] into the [[Thermal exhaust port/Legends|thermal exhaust port]], causing a chain reaction that destroyed the whole [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]]. Following the battle, Starkiller was present in a ceremony when the [[Medal of Bravery/Legends|Medal of Bravery]] was awarded to Skywalker, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]].<ref name="anh">{{Film|IV}}</ref> After that event, Starkiller began to pass on responsibility to the next generation of soldiers, while continuing to serve as a valuable asset in Rebel strategic planning.<ref name="AIR" />

===New Republic===
[[File:Rogues_Gallery.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Starkiller was present at the ceremony of awarding the Medal of Bravery to the Heroes of Yavin.]]
In time, the Rebel Alliance transitioned into the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], and by [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]],<ref name="TNEC" /> when [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] returned from seeming [[Death/Legends|death]] in a [[Cloning/Legends|cloned]] body and set about waging war on the New Republic, Starkiller had once again retired from active duty. When [[Jan Dodonna/Legends|Jan Dodonna]], still serving as a strategist for the Republic, realized that he could not fulfill the commitment that post required by himself, he called upon a number of retired military men, including Starkiller, [[Vanden Willard/Legends|Vanden Willard]], and [[Adar Tallon/Legends|Adar Tallon]], to form an advisory group that jokingly nicknamed itself the "[[Gray Cadre/Legends|Gray Cadre]]." Starkiller and the others used their experience to advise the commanders of the New Republic on vital military areas in a time of extreme crisis.<ref name="DESB" />

Starkiller and the rest of the cadre had their time to shine in the [[Battle of Calamari|Battle of Mon Calamari]] during [[Operation Shadow Hand]]. The advice they gave the New Republic allowed its military to design some of its most successful combat strategies during the battle, and ultimately saved millions of lives. After the Republic's victory, Starkiller and the others returned to a state of semi-retirement, meeting monthly to discuss matters of strategic planning and anticipate the goals of the Empire. If their expertise was needed again, they were prepared to give whatever information and analysis the commanders of the front-line fighting needed.<ref name="DESB" /> Sometime after the battle with Palpatine, Starkiller, once again retired, received a carbon copy of a memo from the Mon Calamari [[Zgorth'sth]] of the newly-formed New Republic [[Department of Threat Assessment]], providing intelligence about a number of organizations in the galaxy that might pose a threat to Republic interests.<ref name="AJ15">{{JournalCite|15|Special Military Unit Intelligence Update}}</ref>

==Personality and traits==
Though retired as a respected Imperial general and a former Warlord of the Empire,<ref name="Warlords" /> when the Rebel Alliance approached Starkiller, the former Imperial official nonetheless chose to join in their fight. Starkiller was one of the Alliance's best, and those who trained under the man reflected Starkiller's ability in their own work.<ref name="AIR" /> After a second retirement, Starkiller did not seek to return to full-time service, content to allow the next generation of officers to come into their own. Starkiller's experience was nonetheless considered invaluable by the New Republic, and along with the others in the Gray Cadre, Starkiller's knowledge of tactics and strategy made a significant difference in the war against the reborn Palpatine. Starkiller remained dedicated to the New Republic even after the immediate crisis ended, forgoing complete retirement to lend services to their continuing fight against the Empire.<ref name="DESB" /> Starkiller had [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and fair skin.<ref name="Insider" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|We decided to treat it as another Pashna Starkiller.|Leland Chee|<ref name="FB">{{Facebook|noprofile=1|url=permalink.php?story_fbid=404388596248739&id=201820953172172|name=Leland Chee|date=May 8, 2012|quote=We decided to treat it as another Pashna Starkiller.|nobackup=1}}</ref>}}
An individual named Pashna Starkiller was first mentioned in [[Michael Allen Horne]]'s ''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]'', published in [[1993]].<ref name="DESB" /> In [[2003]], the ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'' Multiplayer Online game included a [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] named [[Pashna Starkiller (Mon Calamari)|Pashna Starkiller]] among its non-player characters.<ref name="Galaxies">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref> Since no previous source had established Starkiller's physical appearance, gender and species, it was assumed to be the first physical depiction of the character, even though fan reaction ranged from surprise to belief that "Starkiller" was not a name fitting a Mon Calamari.<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=threads/27033618|board=Literature|thread=Pashna Starkiller a Mon Cal?|archiveurl=https://archive.is/BQFtt}}</ref>

In [[2012]], the article [[Rogues Gallery (department)|''Rogues Gallery'']] in [[Star Wars Insider 133|''Star Wars Insider'' 133]] identified one of the Humans present at the Rebel celebration in the [[Great Temple/Legends|Massassi Temple]] at the end of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']],<ref name="Insider" /> portrayed by [[George Stock]],<ref name="SWAStockNotes">{{Blogspot|subdomain=starwarsaficionado|url=2016/02/behind-scenes-celebration-fit-for-heroes.html|name=Star Wars Aficionado|text=Behind The Scenes: A Celebration Fit For The Heroes!}}</ref><ref name="CantinaArcheology">{{YouTube|video=J7ygjomkfXQ&t|text=Star Wars: A New Hope - Cantina Archeology Part 1: Behind The Scenes of the Mos Eisley Cantina - UK|channel=@CredibleNerds|name=The Credible Nerds}}</ref> as Pashna Starkiller, creating further controversy. When asked about the subject, the article's author [[Leland Chee]] explained that it was decided to treat the two Starkillers as separate characters.<ref name="FB" /> ''Galaxies'' had been known for creating such duplicates of existing characters before, attaching [[Near-Human]] [[Zekka Thyne]]'s name to a [[Zekka Thyne (Bothan)|Bothan]] and [[Selonian/Legends|Selonian]] [[Chertyl Ruluwoor (Selonian)|Chertyl Ruluwoor's]] name to a [[Chertyl Ruluwoor (Human)|Human]].<ref name="Galaxies" />

